        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Support ultra thinking level",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds `ultra` as a first-class thinking level when a provider/model advertises that effort.\n\nThis keeps legacy aliases stable: `ultrathink` continues to normalize to `high`; only explicit `ultra` requests use the new level.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Add `ultra` to canonical thinking level types/ranks and session/default-thinking validation.\n- Preserve provider-declared `ultra` in OpenAI-compatible reasoning effort resolution.\n- Fall `ultra` back to the strongest declared compatible effort (`max`, then `xhigh`, then `high`) when unsupported by the selected model.\n- Let `compat.supportedReasoningEfforts` expose provider-declared `max`/`ultra` levels in thinking profiles, rather than only `xhigh`.\n- Update docs and tests for the new level and compatibility behavior.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm exec tsx -e '...'` sanity check covering:\n  - `normalizeThinkLevel(\"ultra\") === \"ultra\"`\n  - legacy `normalizeThinkLevel(\"ultrathink\") === \"high\"`\n  - `ultra` rank is above `max`\n  - OpenAI-compatible resolver preserves declared `ultra`\n  - OpenAI-compatible resolver falls `ultra` back to `max` when `ultra` is not declared\n\nNote: full local vitest/tsc runs were resource-heavy in my clean worktree; CI should provide the authoritative full matrix.\n",
